      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ELITE ONE (1) has been in the minors the last two, the latest showing strong pace early but gathered in and finished a head second over 660m Bendigo in 37.91. Can measure up this time. MEPUNGA DONNA (8) is a talented dog who is a winner of 12 races but missed the frame last time when fourth at Q Parklands (41.99). Solid record here at this trip including four wins. Has performed well from this box with a win and three minor placings to her name from six starts. Has ability and can measure up. MAGIC LOKI (7) was prominent throughout when winning two back then got further back last time but came home hard into third and beaten 6 lengths at this track (30.27). Winning chance. ESPOIR (2) made it two minor placings on the trot when beaten third (30.48) in a Grade 5 H at this track last time out.",
